We're going to start by learning how to play G.  Before we can look at G on the staff, we need to know how to place our fingers on your instrument. It looks a little like this...

Memorize where to put your fingers first.  This diagram looks
confusing at first, but you will get used to it and will find your
notes easily with some practice.
Now let's finally look at G on the staff.  To play G we need to hold three fingers down on our left hand.
